criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  aged 18 and over;

          -  with chronic calcifying pancreatitis;

          -  having already received endoscopic treatment for pancreatic pain related to stenosis
             and / or pancreatic stones;

          -  having given free, informed and written consent;

          -  being affiliated to a social security scheme or beneficiary of such a scheme.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  contraindications to performing an upper digestive endoscopy;

          -  haemorrhagic disease, haemostasis and coagulation disorder (PR <60%, PTT> 40 s and
             platelets <60,000 / mm3;

          -  pregnant or breastfeeding woman;

          -  adult patient protected (guardianship or curatorship), or deprived of liberty by a
             judicial or administrative decision;

          -  person subject to a safeguard measure.
